Busiest routes===\nHeathrow Airport processed 80,884,310 passengers in 2019.<ref name=stats/> [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York's John F. Kennedy International Airport]]&nbsp;was the most popular route with 3,192,195 passengers.<ref name=\"routestats\"/> The table below shows the 40 busiest international routes at the airport in 2019.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 87.5%\"\n|+ '''Busiest international routes to and from Heathrow (2019)<ref name=routestats>{{cite web|url=https://www.caa.co.uk/uploadedFiles/CAA/Content/Standard_Content/Data_and_analysis/Datasets/Airport_stats/Airport_data_2019_annual/Table_12_1_Intl_Air_Pax_Route_Analysis.pdf}}</ref>\n|-\n!Rank||Airport||Total<br>passengers||Change<br>2018 / 19\n|-\n|1||{{flagdeco|US}} [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York\u2013JFK]]||align='right'|3,192,195||{{increase}} 5.2%\n|-\n|2||{{flagdeco|UAE}} [[Dubai International Airport|Dubai\u2013International]]||align='right'|2,333,127||{{decrease}} 10.6%\n|-\n|3||{{flagdeco|Ireland}} [[Dublin Airport|Dublin]]||align='right'|1,855,333||{{increase}} 2.5%\n|-\n|4||{{flagdeco|Netherlands}} [[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam]]||align='right'|1,748,216||{{increase}} 0.1%\n|-\n|5||{{flagdeco|Hong Kong}} [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]]||align='right'|1,612,530||{{increase}} 2.6%\n|-\n|6||{{flagdeco|US}} [[Los Angeles International Airport|Los Angeles]]||align='right'|1,602,892||{{decrease}} 3.3%\n|-\n|7||{{flagdeco|Germany}} [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]]||align='right'|1,548,995||{{decrease}} 0.7%\n|-\n|8||{{flagdeco|Singapore}} [[Singapore Changi Airport|Singapore]]||align='right'|1,526,634||{{increase}} 7.4%\n|-\n|9||{{flagdeco|Spain}} [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|Madrid]]||align='right'|1,476,551||{{increase}} 4.2%\n|-\n|10||{{flagdeco|Germany}} [[Munich Airport|Munich]]||align='right'|1,266,993||{{increase}} 2.0%\n|-\n|11||{{flagdeco|Qatar}} [[Hamad International Airport|Doha]]||align='r