{"title_page": "Barry Gallagher", "text_new": "{{about|the former professional footballer|the anime character|Tekkaman: The Space Knight}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Barry Gallagher\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place = England\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| years1         = 1977\u20131983\n| clubs1         = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1          = 71\n| goals1         = 22\n| years2         = 1982\u20131983\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] (loan)\n| caps2          = 3\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 1983\u20131986\n| clubs3         = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]]\n| caps3          = 115\n| goals3         = 27\n| years4         = 1986\n| clubs4         = [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]]\n| caps4          = ?\n| goals4         = ?\n| years5         = 1986\u20131988\n| clubs5         = [[\u0126amrun Spartans F.C.|\u0126amrun Spartans]]\n| caps5          = ?\n| goals5         = ?\n| totalcaps      = 189\n| totalgoals     = 49\n| manageryears1  = 1988\u20131989\n| managerclubs1  = [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]] (Assistant Manager)\n}}\n'''Barry Gallagher''' is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]]. Active in [[the Football League]] for three clubs between 1977 and 1986, Gallagher made 189 career appearances, scoring 49 goals. After retiring as a player, Gallagher became a football coach.\n\n==Career==\nGallagher began his career with [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] after graduating through their youth system, making 71 appearances in [[the Football League]] between 1977 and 1983.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/bradfordcity/bradfordcity.html|title=BRADFORD CITY : 1946/47 - 2008/09|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> While at Bradford, Gallagher made three appearances on loan at [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/mansfield/mansfield.html|title=MANSFIELD TOWN : 1946/47 - 2007/08|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> After leaving Bradford in 1983, Gallagher signed for [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], making a further 115 League appearances during three seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/halifax/halifax.html|title=HALIFAX TOWN : 1946/47 - 1992/93 & 1998/99 - 2001/02|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> Gallagher later played non-league football with [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]], and in Malta with [[\u0126amrun Spartans F.C.|\u0126amrun Spartans]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=94660 |title=Testimonial match for former Malta, \u0126amrun Spartans player Stefan Sultana |accessdate=30 August 2010 |publisher=The Malta Independent |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301155158/http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=94660 |archivedate=1 March 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> While at \u0126amrun, Gallagher was the top scorer in the [[Maltese Premier League]] during the 1987-88 season, scoring 7 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesm/malttops.html|title=Malta - List of Topscorers|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\nAfter retiring as a player, Gallagher became Assistant Manager to [[Neil Warnock]] at old club [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/6475419.stm|title=Warnock back at Scarborough|accessdate=30 August 2010|date=22 March 2007|author=Pete Oliver|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gallagher, Barry}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mansfield Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scarborough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:\u0126amrun Spartans F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Malta]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:People educated at St. Bede's Grammar School]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about|the former professional footballer|the anime character|Tekkaman: The Space Knight}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Barry Gallagher\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place = England\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| years1         = 1977\u20131983\n| clubs1         = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1          = 71\n| goals1         = 22\n| years2         = 1982\u20131983\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] (loan)\n| caps2          = 3\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 1983\u20131986\n| clubs3         = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]]\n| caps3          = 115\n| goals3         = 27\n| years4         = 1986\n| clubs4         = [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]]\n| caps4          = ?\n| goals4         = ?\n| years5         = 1986\u20131988\n| clubs5         = [[\u0126amrun Spartans F.C.|\u0126amrun Spartans]]\n| caps5          = ?\n| goals5         = ?\n| totalcaps      = 189\n| totalgoals     = 49\n| manageryears1  = 1988\u20131989\n| managerclubs1  = [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]] (Assistant Manager)\n}}\n'''Barry Gallagher''' is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]]. Active in [[the Football League]] for three clubs between 1977 and 1986, Gallagher made 189 career appearances, scoring 49 goals. After retiring as a player, Gallagher became a football coach.\n\n==Career==\nGallagher began his career with [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] after graduating through their youth system, making 71 appearances in [[the Football League]] between 1977 and 1983.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/bradfordcity/bradfordcity.html|title=BRADFORD CITY : 1946/47 - 2008/09|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> While at Bradford, Gallagher made three appearances on loan at [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/mansfield/mansfield.html|title=MANSFIELD TOWN : 1946/47 - 2007/08|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> After leaving Bradford in 1983, Gallagher signed for [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], making a further 115 League appearances during three seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/halifax/halifax.html|title=HALIFAX TOWN : 1946/47 - 1992/93 & 1998/99 - 2001/02|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> Gallagher later played non-league football with [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]], and in Malta with [[\u0126amrun Spartans F.C.|\u0126amrun Spartans]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=94660 |title=Testimonial match for former Malta, \u0126amrun Spartans player Stefan Sultana |accessdate=30 August 2010 |publisher=The Malta Independent |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301155158/http://www.independent.com.mt/news.asp?newsitemid=94660 |archivedate=1 March 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> While at \u0126amrun, Gallagher was the top scorer in the [[Maltese Premier League]] during the 1987-88 season, scoring 7 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesm/malttops.html|title=Malta - List of Topscorers|accessdate=30 August 2010|publisher=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\nAfter retiring as a player, Gallagher became Assistant Manager to [[Neil Warnock]] at old club [[Scarborough F.C.|Scarborough]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/6475419.stm|title=Warnock back at Scarborough|accessdate=30 August 2010|date=22 March 2007|author=Pete Oliver|work=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gallagher, Barry}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mansfield Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scarborough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:\u0126amrun Spartans F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Malta]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Danstarr69", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Gallagher"}
